    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-04-20T16:32:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-04-20T16:32:00-05:00" n="891"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d891">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.56352/2–2753: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 891<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Spain</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d891fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_DUNHAMWB1"
                            >Dunham</persName> and cleared with <persName>Martin</persName> and
                            <persName corresp="#p_BONBRIGHTJCH1">Bonbright</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-04-20T16:32:00-05:00"
                            >April 20, 1953—4:32 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>774. Personal for Ambassador from <persName corresp="#p_BONBRIGHTJCH1"
                        >Bonbright</persName>. Present review contemplated <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                        >FY</gloss> 1954 foreign aid budget, designed achieve greatest possible
                    economies, indicates <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1954 aid figures
                    recommended Embassy’s telegram 683<note n="2" xml:id="d891fn2">
                        <ref target="#d882">Document 882</ref>.</note> and supported in Department’s
                    letter March 6 to <gloss target="#t_DMS1">DMS</gloss>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d891fn3">See <ref target="#d882fn5">footnote 5, <hi
                                rend="italic">ibid</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> no longer feasible.</p>
                <p>Budget review still in progress and no final decisions reached. We fully realize
                    significant relationship this problem has to negotiations. Would therefore
                    appreciate receiving urgently for my guidance your reaction regarding impact
                    each of following possible results of this review would have on continuation of
                    negotiations and their successful outcome.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1)</label>
                    <item>Reappropriation of $125 million (assuming breakdown of $75 million
                        economic aid and $50 military aid) with increase by some small amount, say
                        $25 or $50 million, on military aid side bearing in mind pressure for
                        economies bears most heavily on economic aid side. This appears to us best
                        we might be able to do for <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1954.</item>
                    <label>2)</label>
                    <item>Reappropriation $125 million without any increase.</item>
                    <label>3)</label>
                    <item>Reappropriation only of military aid portion of $125 million.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
